    "updated_at": "2017-01-31T19:19:54Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I don't see how \"slowing-down the unit if the order is a crush order\" would be good at all - such an effect would make no difference if I start microing out infantry crushes by ordering the crusher to move to the cell beyond the infantry from the crusher's POV. Something one has to do in RA2 because that one has this as a locomotor bug, actually.\r\n\r\nMy opinion on this is that slowing down these fast units when they hit the first infantry would be the best way to resolve this because that wouldn't act erratic."
  },
