    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Thats essentially the point.\r\n\r\nWhen a fast unit doesn't get slowed down upon crushing a unit they crush more effectively. These units that do cell to cell turns crush entire packs of 5 easily and units that transition to a new cell do not roll the RNG of dodge chance because they are on the move.\r\n\r\nSo the unit that makes contact with the first set of infantry that has this trait can slow down a bit which at least gives the infantry a chance to dodge.\r\n\r\nMy fault for not explaining it well.\r\n\r\nThe other thing that could be a problem is I don't know if the trait could have a speed setting on it. One speed may work on other units but another speed may not work on the other unit."
  },
